    "notes": "Ethiopia operates a mandatory e-visa or VoA system for virtually all foreign nationals. Only Kenya and Djibouti are explicitly listed as visa-exempt ('Visa Exemptions' section) on evisa.gov.et. Visa on Arrival (tourist visa only) is available for approximately 119 eligible countries listed on evisa.gov.et (paginated React SPA; first 5 countries confirmed on live re-check: Algeria, Angola, Argentina, Austria, Australia). Max stay days for VoA not explicitly stated per-country on the official site. E-visa page confirmed: 30-day (USD 62) and 90-day (USD 152) options both listed. Previous record noted payment exclusions (Cuba, Iraq, Sudan, Yemen, Somalia, North Korea, Afghanistan, South Sudan, Crimea, Syria) but this list was not visible in the June 2026 re-scrape of the tourist page — see gaps. Kenya and Djibouti removed from the visa_on_arrival list (classification fix: they belong only in visa_free)."
